# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env — environment variables for the product browsing backend
#
# WHY A .env FILE?
#   Keeps secrets (database credentials) out of source code. python-dotenv
#   loads this file at startup so the app and seed script can read DATABASE_URL
#   via os.environ without hard-coding anything.
#
# IMPORTANT: Add `.env` to your .gitignore so credentials are never committed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

